# 6. 好きなものを楽しんで

Mizuki: Hmm... What would Shizuku like for her present?
Mizuki's Sister: So many good candidates, but none really stand out above the rest.
Shiho: I'm really sorry about being so indecisive...
Mizuki: Not a problem! Browsing's been super fun, and I really want Shizuku to enjoy what she gets.
Saki: Oh... Hey, they have animal brooches over here!
Mizuki: Look at that! They've got dogs, cats... And they're all really cute!
Mizuki: Does Shizuku have a favorite animal?
Shiho: Umm... She likes these birds called long-tailed bushtits. I'm guessing they don't have those...
Shiho: Also, rabbits...
Mizuki: Rabbits?
Shiho: Something about them brings us together. In the past we've made rabbit-shaped dango, snow rabbits and...
Mizuki's Sister: Really...? Hehe. That's so precious.
Mizuki: Then, let's try looking for one! Rabbits, bunnies...
Mizuki: Aha! Look here! This one's got jewels embedded in its eyes and ears!
Mizuki: It's even got a fluffy cotton ball for a tail!
Saki: Whoa, you're right!
Shiho: It's cute...
Mizuki: Huh?
Shiho: Oh, uhh... Nothing.
Shiho: Anyway, this brooch might be nice... It isn't a gaudy color or anything, so she should be able to wear it on a daily basis.
Mizuki: Really? Woohoo! Then, you wanna go with this?
Shiho: I do. Thank you for all your help.
Shiho: You two also, Saki, Yuki. I really appreciate what you did.
Mizuki's Sister: You're welcome! I'm glad you were able to find something nice for her!
Shiho: Me too. Anyway, I'll take this up to the—
Mizuki: Oh, wait...! They've got that brooch in a few different colors!
Shiho: What?
Mizuki: Hmm...
Mizuki: I think this color would work really well!
Shiho: You think so...? I thought this other one would look nice on her.
Mizuki: No, not her! I was talking about you, Shiho!
Shiho: Me...?
Mizuki: Yeah! Can you try it on for me?
Shiho: No, I'm good... I don't usually wear these sorts of things.
Mizuki: Huuuh? But you just said they're cute.
Shiho: No, I didn't...
Mizuki: What?! Don't lie!
Saki: Whenever we go out shopping together, even though she really likes them deep down, Shiho never tries on anything that she thinks is cute.
Shiho: Saki...!
Mizuki's Sister: To be fair, everyone has their own style. You might like something that you find, but not necessarily want to wear it.
Mizuki: Yeah, true... It's a little unfortunate since I really wanted to see you try this brooch on, Shiho!
Shiho: Anyway, I'm taking Shizuku's brooch up front...
Saki: Oh, I'll go with you! I also found some accessories that I really like!
Mizuki: Then, we'll be waiting outside!
Mizuki: (Still, it's kind of a shame... Shiho really seemed to like these brooches.)
Mizuki: (At the same time, she's more the cool and collected type as opposed to cute and cuddly. So, I kinda get her objections...)
Mizuki: (But you can wear brooches a million different ways. I've gotta think there's a trick out there for getting this brooch to look good on Shiho.)
Mizuki's Sister: Is something the matter, Mizuki...?
Mizuki: Huh?
Mizuki's Sister: You seem unsure about something.
Mizuki: Haha. Nothing gets by you, Sis.
Mizuki: I was just wondering if there are any good ways for Shiho to make use of that brooch we just saw.
Mizuki's Sister: Oh, I see. She could conceivably pin it to a hat or bag without having it stand out too much. She could also turn it into a keychain of some sort!
Mizuki: Yeah, that's what I'm talking about!
Mizuki: Which is why I personally think it's kind of a shame that she isn't getting it. She actually seems to have a soft spot for cute things...
Mizuki: You know that feeling of excitement that comes over you when you put on something you think is cute? How can you not smile, you know...?
Mizuki's Sister: Then, why not tell Shiho that...?
Mizuki: Wait, but... Wouldn't that make me too pushy?
Mizuki: I mean, Sis, you just said it yourself. Everyone has their own style.
Mizuki's Sister: Yes, I did. But she may want to try it out if you tell her about some of the ideas we just talked about, no?
Mizuki's Sister: Also, don't you want her to get more joy from the things that she loves deep down...?
Mizuki: Oh... Yeah, I do.
Mizuki's Sister: Then, why don't you go over to her and give her some suggestions?
Mizuki's Sister: I believe that any person's possibilities are endless. The choice is ultimately Shiho's, but you should at least tell her.
Mizuki: Endless possibilities...
Mizuki: I agree...
Mizuki: Thanks, Sis. I'll go try telling her!
Mizuki's Sister: Okay, good luck!
Mizuki: (Sis really is an amazing person...)
Mizuki: (Now then!)
Mizuki: Hey, Shiho!
Shiho: Huh...?
Mizuki: Um, about that brooch... Mind if I gave you a quick presentation about it?!
Shiho: A presentation...?
Mizuki: Yeah! I get that you think it's a little too cute for you, but I think there's a way to get around that!
Mizuki: For example, instead of pinning it onto your clothes...
Saki: Hey, cool! I never thought about using a brooch as a keychain!
Mizuki: Yeah, I figured that you'd be able to use this brooch more often if it were like this.
Shiho: You have a point... A keychain for my bag does seem a lot better.
Mizuki: See what I mean?
Mizuki: I really love cute stuff like this. Seeing these kinds of things always makes me feel better and gives me the energy I need.
Shiho: Yeah, I think I know what you mean...
Mizuki: So, Shiho, if you like this brooch and think it's cute...
Mizuki: I'm really hoping that you'll get it and wear it in a way that you'd enjoy it!
Shiho: ...
Shiho: Yeah, okay...
Shiho: Then, I'll also get one for myself since it might be nice as a keychain...
Mizuki: Really?! You mean it?!
Saki: Oh! That means you and Shizuku are gonna match!
Shiho: That's beside the point.
Mizuki: Haha! Then, here! Your very own rabbit!
Shiho: Thanks...
Shiho: (We're gonna match... Come to think of it, we always used to wear the same clothes.)
Shiho: (I guess it's still okay every once in a while...)
Saki: Hehe. Shizuku's gonna love your present so much, Shiho!
Shiho: I sure hope so...
